  "script": "830 people, one brunch? In Seattle, a single neighborhood packed 830 people around tables to eat dim sum at the same time — and smashed a Guinness World Record for the largest dim sum gathering ever. Picture it: hundreds of bamboo steamers, clouds of dumpling steam, 830 pairs of chopsticks moving at once. Judges had to actually count every seated eater and verify everyone was served the real thing — no empty baskets allowed. It's part block party, part world record, part the best-smelling crowd on earth. Somehow nobody fought over the last shrimp dumpling. So how do you even feed 830 people dim sum before it goes cold?",
